"n. 严重伤害罪 【英】 n. 严重伤害罪(the intentional mutilation of another's body) 【记】 和maim(伤残)有关；分割记忆：may+hem( 边缘) 【例】 The violent criminal was charged with mayhem. n. 故意严重伤害罪 【记】源于: maim(v 使残废)may＋hem(n 边缘): 也许在边上, 推下去就残废了－伤害罪 【记】近于maim 使残废；音: 谋害某，某指我或某人 mayhem (n.)  late 15c., from Anglo-French maihem (13c.), from Old French mahaigne ""injury, wrong, a hurt, harm, damage;"" related to mahaignier ""to injure, wound, mutilate, cripple"" (see maim). Originally, in law, the crime of maiming a person ""to make him less able to defend himself or annoy his adversary"" [OED]."
